Dear Mihoyo, I think that the 4201 is not only because of network setting, this error is very random that nobody have the exact solution for that. I tried everything but the problem is persist. Something is wrong, please check for this error.

To be able to play this game on phone is unbelievable, hope mihoyo always improve it Update : now i feel burnt out, repeating the same thing over and over, collect ore, commission, domain, it's just never ending loop. At first, it was fun. There were new places to explore, new characters to be gotten, new experiences to try. But now it's gotten to the point where it's hard to even play the game now. Why? Because Mihoyo never innovates and makes it so that the endgame content is severely restrictive and unfun towards F2P's and low spender's. The only thing they actually care about is money, not the community who have been asking them for better changes. The anniversary has only made this feeling a lot worse.

Although being a role playing game, Genshin has lately one of the worst stories I personally have ever immersed myself inside. During the We Will Be Reunited Quest, not only die Paimon repeat everything that happened 5 seconds ago, she completely ruined the mood with the recap at the end. The 2.1 Archon Quest was an illogical mess with no structure at all and other than that, this game is extremely grindy and stingy. (Don't play if you're susceptible to gambling and addiction)

A game that good at the begining but have a very boring end game content. Also stupid and greedy dev.. They didn't care about you or listen to you at all. No matter how much you spend money or do anything to support the game, they never gift back to you. They just did what ever is profitable to them. I never feel being unappreciated like this in my whole gaming experience.

PROS: Incredible devs (visuals, lores, designs) and music composers. Fast and regular updates every 6 weeks. Super grindy with time-gated contents for those that are into it. CONS: Incredibly terrible corporate with blantant disrespect to their players. Silent PR, many character bugs that don't directly affect their sales still not fixed. Efficiently scummy and predatorial business tactic, be careful kids, they care about your wallet, not yourself.

The game itself is really beautiful and well made, gameplay isn't that complex and the game is an F2P friendly game, the communities are also great. The problems are, - End game, it starts to feel like a chore rather than a game that you play "to have fun". - The rewards are such a joke, - Lacks of events, the update is too long - Lacks of Co-op activities - Everything is RNG in this game it's not even funny anymore.

i still give it two stars because while i play to get to endgame, it was fun exploring until it isnt. with endgame content that already lacking as is, the anniversary that supposed to bring people together and play isnt here, no emphasis on co-op events, story felt rushed, character kits not working as intended. this just isnt it chief, i dont really care about rewards, what i really trying to say is about the content (mainly communal events) thanks for the year, its been fun.

Terrible optimization even on high-end device, poorly designed predatory gacha systems that will revolve around credit card, time gated gameplay that forces you to spend daily to do chores in order to have decent funds for the gacha, did i not mention as well a gacha-based equipment (artifact) stats that requires either a dumb good luck or spending 6 month getting a good one, terrible and repetitive enemy bosses especially design-wise,Min. reward on events. +Good Map design, Especially Liyue.

Enjoy the game at a slow pace, don't rush it. It's best to enjoy with friends so you can experience the scenery and gameplay together. And don't gacha if you mind about your wallet, it's addictive. Edit : endgame is boring, the developer not really giving enough affection for their community of players

Even though the game in itself is pretty good if a bit lacking in some areas (progression, missing end game), I want to rate it 1 stars as the tactics used for extracting money from players are atrocious, even for gacha games. There are multiple currencies, intransparent conversion ratios and with very low rates characters and weapons can cost 100s of Euros to get or the fact that artifacts are 100% RNG with the relevant substats being less likely I can't recommend this game to others. I'll give it 2 stars anyways as the atmosphere and the soundtrack in some places is amazing (also available on Spotify though)

The game itself is pretty good to be honest in terms of exploration, graphics, gameplay. etc. But the major problem that me and other people are having is how this game doesn't state any clear signs of it being caring to its community. For further information in order to strengthen this statement is for the current anniversary reward itself. Many players have been supporting the game for over a year and many have put their dedication and savings into this game as well, but the way on how they repay us back for whole year of endless support is a huge slap in the face. Not to mention the game itself is actually quite grindy and in order to get the characters that you wanted you need to do gacha where the gacha rates itself is really terrible.

truly an amazing game, I'll be honest. the graphics, the music, the story and the whole open world experience. although I feel like they've fallen off recently, the recent lore feels more rushed, some of the kits of newer characters could do better and would it really hurt to give better rewards? it feels disrespectful to the community. also the prizes for art and cosplay contests could definitely be better, the art and cosplay is worth so much more.

They kept releasing bad kit for awesome designed character like Kokomi and Yoimiya. It such a shame bcs I love their design. They don't even buff characters and electro. And the anniversary rewards... Ugh. It's REALLY dissapointing. Idk why a such big company doesn't give a great anniversary rewards. We won't ask more than a free five stars character from standart banner or a free five stars weapon that we can choose and 20 wishes. It'll be ENOUGH if they give us that, not only 10 wishes.

The game is fun but alot of things are limited even if you pay... And either u are super lucky or have tons of money to get 5* characters or weapons. If u dont care about those stuff then good luck getting through spiral abbyss at the higher level.. their stories, graphic and soundtrack is super amazing but don't spend your money for this game, not worth it. My friend who play for free has more 5 star characters than me who spent almost $100. Very sad indeed.

It's a really good game that has everything but as a mobile player, I suffered a lot of lags and I would say I'm slightly disappointed with the lack of content for end game players (AR 55 right now). The latest story kinda seem like it lacks something. Also for a huge company with a gacha themed game, the one year rewards are kinda bad just 10 fates ain't enough for a 5* unless super lucky. It's a good game to spend time if you got nothing to do. It's like mini playground. Lovely character and world. Unfortunately. The developer never responded to community feedback. All radio silence and that caused this review bomb...

Great visuals for a mobile game, decent story (later on) and incredible music that blows any competition away. The problem comes when you enter endgame and also the gacha. Endgame only consists of farming domains, doing dailies, and or doing events, which are pretty much always the same in nature. Early on however the game is very enjoyable and there's plenty of loot and rewards (if you're willing to spend the time getting those rewards). As a endgame player getting the game's premium currency "primogems" is very difficult, even when you're logging in daily and doing all event. It seems to me that the developers don't realize how scarcity of primogems ruins the game in the long run. E.g. having to daily play for MONTHS just to get a 50% chance to get a character that you want. And if you don't get it you have to wait 6 - 9 months for the character to return. Honestly I think if they doubled the amount of primogems you get from everything it would make the game a lot more enjoyable. Either that, or boost the % rates of 5*s. (Genshin has of the worst gachas in terms of %rates) recently the game had a 1 year anniversary and as a gacha game the community expected big rewards and events. Instead Mihoyo gave us an event that has a 10% to give as something actually useful and also a ton of fan art/cosplay/memories ‚Äúcontests‚Äù which offer real life prizes (mostly Apple products) worth ~17K USD, the funny thing is that Mihoyo spent millions on hashtags on twitter (icons that appear next to the hashtags), which kind of shows what priority the developers have. The ‚Äúcontests‚Äù also tells players to basically ‚Äúspam‚Äù their submissions, which serves as free advertisement for the game. There has also been a recent influx of "bad/wip" characters making it into the live build of the game. The problem with this is that people save up for these characters for months (or spend ridiculous amounts of money) to get them. I'll finish this review by saying I'm very unsure about the future of this game and its developer. Hopefully Mihoyo starts listening to its players and make changes for the better, otherwise I HIGHLY recommend not spending any money on this game. FINAL RATING 2/5

The event, quest, and the story update are getting repetitive. All the side quests are becoming more boring with long pointless conversation and lack of new animation, without interesting animation and weird convo is just not interesting. No updates on home pot and friendship mission. The only things that they care about is the gacha system, it is becoming harder with fate system and off rate for weapon. The open world is becoming empty for old player.

The game was good, but that only last the first few months. Been a year already but there is no really increase in QoL. World setting and exploration is top notch, but story and character development is getting worse by time. In-game currency is hard to get, not so much appreciation for paid players yet alone f2p players. Too make matter worst, Anniversary is treated as non existent. Better avoid this game as better games will probably come soon in 2022.
The game itself is fine. However, the lack of communication from the devs is really concerning, especially if you're going to spend money on the game.

The game was good. Dragonspine and Golden Apple Archipelago updates are my favourites. The problem was with Inazuma release. It was perfect at the start. But the ending was not. Kinda rushed. They just killed off a character with supposedly good history on a whim without proper story or development. Characters that were supposed to be great have so little role in the conclusion of the story. Gameplay is good. Art, design, and music are all nice. But characters and story seem to lack depth.

A very nice experience at early game, mid to end is just straight up boring. Feels greedy from the start, bad artifact obtain/upgrade system, and on top of it the anniversary reward (oh boy). Listen to the playerbase, they're the one hyping up the game.

Addictive gameplay, but still lack of end game content. The last archon quest feels rushed and it impacted some of the new characters. Making it forgettable. Maybe make a second war or something so we can see what the new characters can do and care for them. Also bad anniversary reward. Hope this helpful.

First the story is kinda rushed, I didn't know enough about Kokomi and Gorou, just like Xinyan in Liyue. Second, I didn't feel the war in Inazuma, there's only one war scene, you need to add more scene, some all out battle with many enemies with soldiers clashing on the background, and maybe some quest that shows strategic war moves like sabotaging supply line, etc.

Gameplay: interesting gameplay, you can wander free, soove puzzle, hunt for chests, finish quests. Untill you run out of them. But every update has events so it's not as boring as login, do tasks, log out. Music: high quality music, chef kiss lvl of nice. Story: as of 2.1 the quality of story is falling, pls don't neglect these as it's one of the main selling point of these kind of game.

I paid for welkin and battlepass once, and it's already a price for a full game from other developer, yet not only I can only experience 2 5 stars characters, but also lack of content and story progression. you tease Inazuma onward behind a further update for your marketing scheme, yet the player abandons the premise of the story to find their sibling with stupid time wasting event without progressing the story.

The art department for this game is top notch! Beautiful orchestrated music, fantastic character designs, satisfying sound effects, great voice acting in all languages and the open world is a joy to explore. The fun gameplay and having few game breaking bugs is appreciated too. Recently however, the last few limited characters have lackluster kits or have compatibility issues with existing characters. Also, the PR department is ruining the reputation of the development studio. The 1st year anniversary is pretty much non-existent and there's little to no communication, which is a problem that's been going on for over half a year now. As a long time player and spender, I feel unappreciated and that the studio cares more about profit than the player base that made them a household name in the first place. As things currently stand, I can't recommend this game to new or returning players.

It's really good while you're working through the story content. If this was sold/billed as a complete RPG it would be a fairly satisfactory game. The problem is that is a live service game, and there's just not much to do after you clear all the story content. The endgame rewards are super grindy and super thin, and the company just doesn't really respect their players at the end of the day. It's not even set up to work as a fair weather game though like Destiny/etc are, you can't go away for a few weeks without falling behind.

This game definitely seems to have started as a passion project and, at least through the early stages, is an impressive undertaking. But I don't really have high hopes for it going forward. While the art and music teams are still 100% on point, all other aspects of the game feel as though they've been left with a skeleton crew. Character balance has gone out the window, the writing quality has plummeted, the new parts of the world feel emptier and unfinished, unfixed bugs and frustrations abound. Some characters have had fundamental parts of their abilities bugged into non-functionality for *months*! It really does bring to mind abandoned early access Steam games with developers that sadly bite off more than they can chew - but with MiHoYo's success, they really should be able to do better. Adding to this sense of abandonment is MiHoYo's complete silence on all these matters. Every now and then they've put out a pithy tweet or a clever joke, but actual communication is essentially nonexistent. The community worldwide is just kinda left spinning their wheels wondering if anything is even being looked at regarding the issues we're all having. We all want to understand! We want to give them the benefit of the doubt! We'd love it if they told us they were having trouble, or that some major refactoring was necessary, or something like that. But... there's nothing at all from them. It really feels as though the community just straight-up doesn't exist to whoever's in charge of PR. Anyway, yeah. Starts off fine, but don't expect too much in the way of continued support. I'd say appreciate the time you have with it, but don't spend money and don't get attached.

The game is fun initially, but soon that dries up and you are then only allowed to progress for like 5-10 minutes a day. This can be extended with RMT. I have never played a gacha game which allowed you to play so little at a time. Also, the reddit and discords attached to the game are tightly censored to keep players in the dark about the lack of meaningful content. This is the only place where players can even express dissatisfaction. The gameplay is fun but very very limited, coupling that with the VERY high prices for gacha rolls, I cannot recommend this game.

If you're into games that are all take and no give, then Genshin Impact is the game for you! The game itself is well presented, with nice clean graphics, decent gameplay and an interesting array of characters, albeit most of them are trapped in exclusive banners that disappear for extremely long periods of time for no real reason, other than a sense of false exclusivity. The feedback provided doesn't really seem to have filtered down into the areas that need to see it, if it has even been looked at by the company at all, and it almost feels like a level of arrogance is on display when it comes to handling the game. About the only thing that has been improved upon is that events don't sap what little resin (the energy equivalent that is used to receive rewards from certain content) you get in the game. There also seems to be a severe lack of player appreciation. In comparison, I've seen similar types of games come out and provide above and beyond what has been shown by Genshin on even half-anniversaries. While I know each game is different and shouldn't provide the exact same kinds of rewards, I would at least expect something beyond a pat on the back and essentially a demand for payment of the rewards they have on display in the forms of competitions for art, etc. It is a game that came out at a very opportunistic time when everyone was needing that extra thing to do when everything was in lockdown, and I believe the management are still riding on the coattails of that popularity, which I feel has begun to show the horrible, greedy side of the corporate teams behind these kinds of ventures. It is worth a look, but if you respect your time and your wallet, I would recommend coming back when the game has hit further milestones.

I wish mihoyo would buckle down and give this game the love and attention it deserves but who knows as of right now. Game was amazing at first, but it seems like the company running the game now is completely different from the one at launch. There was more communication, character kit issues were actually resolved (instead of just being identified), and the character playstyles were straight forward and more or less well-designed. Now, bugs with characters are identified but are unresolved, the player base communication is practically non-existent when it comes to addressing concerns, and more often than not, the latest characters being released are nowhere near well-designed nor as powerful as the characters before (e.g. Kokomi being barely more useful than a free 4-star character, and Raiden being incompatible with characters of her own element, despite her kit being designed to be synergistic with them) Its obvious that the leadership strategy now is just to focus on milking the reputation they garnered at launch until people stop spending. And maybe, hopefully, only after all the goodwill has faded away, will the leadership finally start giving the playerbase the appreciation they deserve, if any of us are still around. I know I won't be.

I'm going straight to the point when I say Genshin Impact is one of the best games i've played in a while. It is really hard to believe that such game can be played for free. However, i've come a long way since the first day i played this game, and currently as an endgame player, there is NOTHING to do. I could use my daily resin to farm artifacts but tbh it is hardly rewarding. In my opinion, genshin lacks end game content. It lacks the system/feature that allows an RPG game to compensate the endgame player base, such as power grinding, lifeskills, marketplace, etc. To be fair, there are upsides of not having this stuff. One of them is allowing other new/low level players to catch up, by not rewarding player by how much time they grind through a game. This is beneficial for players that have irl jobs but still want to play the game without feeling left out. However, as a late game player, it really sucks to be passionate/really into a game, that honestly when I logged in, I don't know what else to do. 5* characters that give players the reason to play the game (to raise, build and enjoy) are so hard to get. And frankly, even the 4* characters are not easy to get (because to be on-par with a 5* or even decent, you need their constelations). And honestly, I've no clue what went on their minds regarding the anniversay gift. Is Mihoyo purposely trying to troll us? Is this a form of power move by them? (considering they know most of us will still play the game even though they give minimal rewards and considering genshin has yet to have a equal competitor) People are arguing that they shouldve given us a free 5*. Honestly, it is arguably a good thing. the 5* is an off banner character anyways, so how does giving each player the choice of one of those characters so hard? Does the opportunity-cost cost you that much mihoyo? Why can't you just give us a blank banner? where people can summon whatever the hell they want? It litterally wont hurt you in any way. It is literally free real estate. People are saving their primogems because they're not summoning for Kokomi, what stop you from giving us what we want? At the end of the day, all I want is an explanation. Why do you give use that much rewards for the anniversary? Do you think that much is worth? Just address all of our questions Mihoyo. Right now, you're like the an Airline that cancels our flight, and left us in the dark, on what on earth is really happening?
replyContent: We'd like to thank all Travelers for your continued support and love of Genshin Impact! We will continue to provide you with more high-quality game content. I just hope for the best for this game because i love it so much! And I hope dev will communicate more to their player base. Happy 1st Anniversary Genshin!

Combat system needs Quality of Life improvement. Such as, an option setting to lock camera zoom level, because the camera tends to automatically zooming in during combat, and it is very difficult to zooming out using pinch gesture on mobile, it is also a tedious activity as it happens every time. The other thing is the option to turn off the 5-star Elemental Burst special camera view, because it can be disorienting and it adds more trouble to re-adjust the camera to the comfortable view.

It's good that Mihoyo doing damage control right now by giving a bundle as a reward. However, this kind of solution is not good long term. Mihoyo needs to improve their public relation and communication to its players or else whenever an incident like this occurs, people will back to review bombing again until Mihoyo pacify them with rewards. Lack of communication and transparency is not good. This only prove that Mihoyo still green as a company.

edit: damage control has been done for anniversary, they gave us free items that was supossed to be sold as a bundle, which im grateful for. but the main problem still exists, it's not about the amount of rewards, but it's the communication between genshin and the community. communication is really bad to the point where none of this would happen if mihoyo would just be transparent to us rather than censoring people's voices on platforms such as discord reddit and hoyolab.

Pros: Great gameplay, beautiful music and graphics. Cons: the gacha rate, limited resin/energy system, and the RNG that are really horrendous. You need to spend $300 to get a guaranteed limited character, also everything is RNG in this game (item drops, upgrade material drops, character level up and talent materials, artifacts farming, even artifact stats upgrade is RNG) It's really bad that you need to spend weeks or even months to build a proper character for end game.

Okay so I'm having some hopium for the anniversary rewards now, but still there's a lot of aspects of the game that could be better. Such as the resin system is bad, controller support for android nowhere to be seen, we need end game content besides the abyss. And on top of that we need better communication between the devs and the players!

I like how sentimental the bgm and story. Moreover the open world it's just beautiful. So many voice actor i love in this game, so far I'm happy playing this game. I meet nice friends who makes me still play this game. I hope for better gameplay and story or side quest we can get. I'm sorry to do this Mihoyo BUT your way to compensate and treat your player is bad. 100 primogems can't even pull 1 banner and bad anniversary event EVER! I still play for fun no longer Top-Up in this game again.

This game is honestly the one of the most memorable RPG games that I've ever played. I had even spent a noteworthy sum of money in the in-app purchases as a token of my appreciation for the game. However, minor problems that have existed since the beginning have ballooned into a serious problem. The farming of artifacts, talent books, etc rely on luck, just like its annoying gacha wish system. The quality of story writing has degraded recently. And the poor anniversary rewards just worsen it.

Thank you for the anniversary gift, the event was even worse than the previous event. For the gameplay itself I'm quite satisfied, it's just that the pity system is not very beneficial for some f2p. Moreover, there are many hackers, in my opinion, first eradicate the hackers who are roaming around rather than leakers, prioritize players over you, because I really hope this game continues to grow and many players want to play this game.
replyContent: We'd like to thank all Travelers for your continued support and love of Genshin Impact! We will continue to provide you with more high-quality game content. If Travelers encounter problems during their adventures, please don't hesitate to contact us via the in-game feedback channel. Your gaming experience and suggestions are always important to us.

content: The game is interesting, good graphics, awesome characters, the story was good at first but starts to feel really boring when Inazuma comes. The first time you got into this game was awesome, but the more you progress, the more awful it becomes. Events are also just nothing special anymore. Everything you do for endgame is just commission, spending resin, and THAT'S IT. Nothing more. Please be considerate and make fun contents for everyone and I will increase the rating.

Honestly im playing this game since its been released. But the game is not as fun as i played it back in the days, and honestly the rewards that are given to the player are quite horrible but i think it's fine. But overall the gameplay is fun and i really enjoyed it, but for me this game is not the same as it used to be, thank you.

The game itself is great. The problem is the gacha aspect. The game, contrary to most gachas is a real game and not just a cash grab. However, due to its predatory nature, this can turn into a problem since newer players are not prepared to face many pitfalls of gacha. Other issue is the lack of feedback from miHoyo. They tend to not listen to the community, and as result end doing some strange decisions. A good example of this is the anniversary, at first people were upset that the rewards were lackluster. Short after, they decided to do community events where they would ask for promotion / work from the players and as trade, they wound only give rewards to a small few (chose at random). Finally, the straw that broke the camels back (for most of the community) was the constant censure of any sort of criticism in most platforms.

Incredibly predatory pricing scheme, where after your initial monthly purchase, you will get up to ten times less premium currency per dollar spent. It is hard to overstate just how maliciously designed the monetization system is, so I strongly encourage you to look into the rates for "Genesis Crystals" per dollar spent before you consider playing this game. If you are F2P, you will constantly be starved for these. The game is fun, beautiful, and has amazing story and music, but I cannot in good faith recommend new players to sign up because of the gross severity of the aforementioned issue.

Game is good. I used to give it 2 stars but I will give 3 now that we received a direct reward to our mailbox haha. At the late game, I still think resin is too pricey and the amount of luck we need for artifact is enormous. Inazuma's enemies are strong while I am stuck with lvl 90 characters without a good artifact. I do domain a lot but my luck is just bad. Not to mention Inazuma's puzzle is making my brain hurt.

I still love the game, despite it's bad system. So i will turn blind eye towards the event also, despite my disappointment and dissatisfaction. But people does say "You rip what you sow." So i hope the developer will consider the wish of the customer and consider a little in the future despite of being greedy. The opinion and the criticism of your player/customer is one of the factor of what makes this game can survive for this 1 years. Happy anniversary to Genshin Impact. Wish you were better.

Here, my honest review after 1 Year Anniversary. The game was good and all but 1 big problem is the dev itself doesn't interact with the community. They just living in the shadow, if you compare it to other dev for example RIOT Games.They have a specific blog for what content to be expect in the future and also get in touch with the community. If Mihoyo do that we won't be bombarded review, we just want transparency what's type of content in the future. Just give us a Roadmap..

Great graphics with an amazing story. Lovable characters. MOST content can be easily beat with 4 star characters. After you've gone through the story all you really have left is farming artifacts which gets really old FAST. Daily grind with little to no rewards. I don't even bother pulling for new banner characters because that means I'll need to farm more artifacts.

Gameplay is okay. Enjoyable combat that has challenging moments. Beautiful characters, and interesting story. Those characters all gated by gacha of course. Devs really dropped the ball on their 1 year anniversary gifts to the community. Out of all the gacha games, (AzurLane, Bandori, Love Live, PriCon, ArkKnights, etc) I've played, this is perhaps one of the worst ones. Not even guaranteed 5 star character from the base release pool. Not even a free new skin or free weapon of choice. Worst part of it all is that the devs seem to be flat out ignoring or sometimes straight up silencing any of these complaints, thinking were just gonna move on when new content comes out. It all really just feels like a slap in the face to the community.

It's a great game, and I've been playing for a while and it has great visuals, great stories, and so much more. The problem is that they rewarded us, the players who got them so many awards, an absolute joke of an anniversary gift. It's actually really bad it's not even decent. I get more rewards from doing missions than the actual anniversary gift.

Beautifull game but this recent update are very ..dissapointing. Newest inazuma 5 star characters are very underwhelming (raiden, yoimiya, especially kokomi) The archon quest in this update is also underwhelming.. good story but executed poorly, how did Teppei an NPC are more relevant than the other characters like kokomi, sara, gorou in the story. The devs are ignoring our complaints.

I loved it in the beginning. The story line is amazing as well as the flow of the game. Sadly, it seems that as time pass by, MHY kind-of neglect simple things in th game. Also, the anniversary rewards is really sad, since it just seems like we as early players were not appreciated enough as we bring more people into the community. Please kindly try to take the feedback, we're just sad.

Have stopped playing since around 3 months ago (before inazuma release) after finding the gameplay boring cause mostly doing repetitive grinding. Characters pretty much your average gacha(3/5) but graphics is epic(5/5). Just one thing that drive me nuts is the fact that you cant improve on pretty much anything unless you pay more : resin limiting your grinding activity, characters talent requires you get more than one copy, while both rate or rewards arent helping this flaw(1/5).

Downsides: 1. Needs powerfull gaming phone to enjoy the graphics. 2. Phone became too hot. 3. Unable to play with controller. Combine this with point #2 = uncomfortable gaming experience because you have to hold a hot phone while playing. Best mmorpg game i've ever played on phone. Edit: Good start, nothing to do at the end. Too much characters and weapons, too few resources to upgrade them, too much time needed to grind them.

Here for the lore but they ruined it too by making too much date w/female characters and let's not forget the latest archon quest(2.1 ver) where they decided to do lazy writing and rush things out they also kept changing stuff with the product (characters) they release and most of the time it's make things worse cause instead changing it for the better they nerf them.

Very fun and stunning game with lots of quests, lore, and exploration with solid game mechanics. But needs more repeatable simple content in between updates and better communication between the community and company (I'd give it a 4 star if mihoyo starts addressing/explaining these issues)

Great game with beautiful graphics, perfect for casuals but not a good timewaster since progress is severely time restricted. Another problem is the slow content release but it certainly gets better with every new release. Would have given 5 stars if genshins marketing team communicated more with its fanbase

I have been playing since Klee's rerun banner. It's a very fun game, and I really like it. Genshin is the first game that has made me really addicted to. Recently, I've seen alot of people complaining about the anniversary rewards. I have to admit, it sucks. The resin refresh rate sucks as well. Unless you have another game to cure your boredom on this stingy game, you're good to go. If you're wondering, my rating used to be 5 stars.

Inazuma story is 100% disappointing. Need 3 days for 1 pull without welkin. Player suggestions are not heard, and that leads the player to massive scale protest. Bad storage management. (Heard you can free 3GB in PC ver if you remove the unused files..). Removes player's freedom to change name and signature out of blue. The list goes on....

At the beginning, i really love this game but as the game progress to endgame. It just become daily login,spend resin, do daily quest and expedition. Also there is no ingame daily login which is strange for gacha game. Pls reduce resin regen rate and chest respawn. Another thing to point out is mihoyo is so cheap for primogem. Best app 2020 = no rewards Annivesary = no rewards Half anni? ,100 days ?. Cygames is more reliable for the rewards.

Very fun adventure RPG with decent story and nice combat. Though beware, the main part of the story is only 10-20 hours long and after your run out of that the game simply become a boring daily grind. The energy system recharge VERY slowly and the gacha is a bit more expensive compared to other games. 90% of the content is in AR 1-35 while the rest up to AR 60 is just a very slow grind. You need to wait 5 hour to get enough energy to do 1 world boss. Also no controller support.

Great graphics, nice gameplay, interesting plot and stories. - MiHoYo, I hope you increase your communication with the community and improve with your game while taking into account the community's suggestions. Genshin community, I hope this behaviour doesn't repeat again, especially the threats and 1* rating towards other games.

I really love this game . The graphics were amazing. I really thought this game was going far, but now the devs arent listening to the community. Whats next the anniversary, when people complained the silenced us community. I dont want any rewards but at least make an event or a supries or even say thank you for anniversary. And now the apology is just giving a bundle that was supposed to be $30 due to backlash. At least apologize or make confirmation on WHY you silenced us. How pathethic mihoyo

I love this game so much. I love the characters, the story, the world, the events and the little details. But once you reach AR 55, everything becomes repetitive. Daily commission, domains, maybe a little bit of exploring and weekly bosses every Monday. It gets boring really fast. But at least the events are fun sometimes.

Great game and all, but although anniversary is disappointing I'm more disappointed with the incredibly rushed and cut content in Inazuma story. Especially when it's SO obvious 'the war' is basically just end out of nowhere before anything even start. Months waiting and for half-assed storyline like this? Disappointed is just understatement for what I'm feeling rn..

I genuinely loved this game since its release but lately it has been poorly managed. Recently released and old characters are underwhelming, the new story felt rushed, anniversary rewards are barely anything and the lack of communication between the player base and Mihoyo is almost non existent. Please address and acknowledge these issues the community have been expressing.

While the game is indeed amazing especially the soundtracks and the world teyvat, there is a lot of small things that annoy me such as: gacha, artifact RNG, redundant dailies, lack of QOL updates, management of the game and a lot more.

Game's fine. Good grapics, exploration and all. Progression felt quite rough and can be all over the place and end-game is very disappointing as there's basically none. My gripe is that publisher don't really want to communicate when something went wrong and felt quite out of touch.

Super beautiful game, used to be 5 stars until the company management make a weird decision to not giving the players (their target market) great rewards to celebrate their games anniversary, weird indeed.

The game was good but resin system is sucks like we cant even play the game for 1 hour straight, we cant upgrade our characters and so much more we cant do due to the resin systen. I wish mihoyo listen to the community to fix this system ASAP like faster resin recharge system could be very helpful. I rather bought a 40$ games that i can play anytime without energy limitation. This is so dumb

The game is fine. Idk why people bomb the review just because the reward were too little. I mean genshin is still a year take it 2-3 year's they will give a good reward in anniversary because maybe the game is declining and they want to attract player. Tbh the game is quite gacha friendly it does have the "pity" system. Some gacha game doesn't have that and some game doesn't have that guarantee reward.

Everything crumbled down since 2.1 update, I honestly am dissapointed that Inazuma's Act 3 Archon quest didn't go well, it felt way too rushed and every build up in the story was useless, miHoYo, you should realize that the story only happens for once and cannot be changed, I am sorry if this is a selfish review but I cannot help but to think that the opportunity got wasted. I do hope that the story will go on track again. Although players finally got their anniversary rewards, they still demand attention. They want some fixes like Eula's first to second attack animation, when Eula does her first normal attack, she swings her claymore upwards, but the problem is, when she does her second normal attack, there is no animation of Eula turning to second normal attack position, she just flips completely 180 degrees and the frames were skipped. Also, Raiden and Beidou battle interaction is pretty messed up, when Raiden using burst during Beidou's burst duration, Raiden can't trigger Thunderbeast's Targe dmg when she does normal or charged attack during Musou Isshin state. Please do fix the problem if it's possible. Thank you.

Everything is made with perfection. The scenery, the music, the lore and the game mechanism are quite astounding. Although there are quite minor bugs and in-game issues, fortunately the devs are really open and responsive in making this game better. This game is more F2P friendly than I thought. But recently the quality of the story is degrading, especially the new character, Kokomi, is not really well written. Since release, the game only fixes the description of the skill, not the mechanism.

Great game, but need to rebalance everything about character so everyone not dependable with dps character than other type character. Too many rng system that make playing at end game so boring because some bad rng luck. Need to expand "End Game" feature because its been 1 year the game launched and many people almost reached the highest lv

content: I loved and enjoyed the game at first. I was one of the whales of this game. From weeklin, top up, battle pas I've always bought from scratch. It's been 1 year since I've played this game, for now just once a year it doesn't give a single appropriate present. I regret that I wasted so much money. But I thank you for the experience and the good game. It's just that I'm very disappointed as the game gets more and more greedy. Thankyou.

it's great for the storyline, but bad for the endgame, nothing good, repetitive, WORST anniversary in a gacha game i have ever played. No actual way to farm premium currency ( 60 primos daily 160 to summon 1x). WORST summon rating i mean summon 1x for 160 is literal hell, well you need summon at least 75x for soft pity and if you are not lucky ? 90x. OH NO YOU ARE REALLY NOT LUCKY, cause the first 90x isn't the guarantee 5 stars from the banner. there you have it, good luck :)

content: 3months of playing this game. Enjoyable, good graphic, but the gacha system is very stingy i mean com'on 90pulls till get 5* char?? And there is a "rate off" ffs.. pls make it to 50pulls then i'll be happy to spend my money. & btw the aniv reward is killing the game.

it's a great game, has great graphics, and character designs too. however the drop rates for 5 star items or characters are very low, and the RnG on artefact domains are very bad too, I didn't say I wanted a def or an hp artifact. If you were to lvl up your artifacts you would probably get def substats or hp because it's just that bad, I would literally cry after a def or hp substat gets upgraded instead of critrate or crit dmg.

I've been playing almost a year (355 days). Almost never stop grinding artifact and material. Always buy welkin and battle pass. Nothing special on the anniversary. Just some reward that equal like daily mission. And just busy releasing some ad video on youtube and order player to share some link for more (small) reward. Maybe it's not anniversary, but AD-niversary

I love this game and I still do. But after spending countless hours and money into this game, the rewards that they give us back is really lacking. Edit: I forgot to mention about how they treat players who spend less differently compared to players who spend a fortune. F2P players have to grind 10√ó more than whales who can just swipe to get what they want. Please listen to the whole community and not just the players who would fill your pockets.

Second part of inazuma's story feels very rushed. It's sad because the story has the potential to be developed even more. There are so many characters that being abandoned or forgotten, resulting in a very bad character development. The game always release new char every 20 days, in which most of them don't have any real impact on storyline. This is mainly because the main/archon story is very rushed, making the characters ingame get less screen time.

This my third review after you mistook them as "bot spam". The gameplay and the graphics of this game are beyond any other mobile games. But the issue lies with it being a gacha game. There are a lot of old characters with unfixed bugs, not enough end game content, and the cost to get a certain 5 star character is too high. The focus of genshin is not to improve players' experience, but to make more money.

I really love this game, but recently there's nothing to do in-game. Moreover, the company finally show their greed. 1st anniversary rewards? What a joke Edited, they finally gave us some items but still, the company's communication with community needs improvement

Been 1 year playing this game and theres not really much improvement. Resin is still an issue, electro element remain sitting at the very bottom, bad characters balance (inazuma characters), rewards ingame are miniscule, spiral abyss is getting harder and harder yet the rewards remain the same, and lastly no real endgame content...

this game is great if it's not the best. combining magnificent music with beautiful art to create majestically huge environment to enjoy. that being said, genshin didnt offer much activity to do with it aside for the first time reward. there are lot potential features that ends up as a gimmick and become meaningless, the open-world itself is one of examples. you can enjoy all the contents for the first time, once you've done all, there's nothing you can do with the game except chore.

So far even though with my poor device, genshin has become one of the game that sticks to my heart, also the fact that genshin is one of THE BEST game ever exist, but how you TREAT the player is very poorly, despite having many influence, the reward anniversary is very...

The game needs to be improved for end game repeatable activity that doesn't need resin cost. Roadmap should be well communicated for upcoming updates. Female Character story quest should be more than just fan service. All the Inazuma female character quest are like going on dates with them. What happened with good story writing and lore like the quests of the male characters? Mihoyo should start considering how to be more transparent towards the community and step down from their high horse

Add more diverse banner on every patch with rerun character or just put old 5* character in the standard banner pool. Making everything limited time is annoying. Hopefully this would be implemented in the next patch.

Please optimize more on mid phone, because my phone is goes warm-hot much faster than before Please adding render area limit feature, adding fully Vulkan support, etc that can be friendly for low-mid device

I really love the graphics, osts and characters gameplay, but the problem is everytime i do coop in a domain, it keeps make me waiting for the enemies to show up, and the same thing happened when i do spiral abbys, each chamber will take around 30 seconds, waiting for the enemies to show up, sometimes this make me frustrated because i keep repeating the level to get stars, i use android to play this game, and not sure if the others also experienced the same but i hope you can fix this

Solid rpg. Good graphics, free to play, and even if the combat is not the best it's still fun and the story is actually decent (even if unfinished). Sadly there is a downside. Gacha elements aside, after you got to near max level, everything is just too grindy. The only way to make your characters better beyond this point is upgrade your artifacts which is pure RNG and is also time locked. I understand that any game wants to keep their playerbase but this is just borderline addiction inducement

Greedy. I've been playing this game around two weeks after its release and not a single day missed not playing it. I spent some money for the welkin moon and Battle pass so far but after what they did... or didn't do in the first year anniversary, I will no longer spend anything on this game.

Don't delete my comment. Your gacha system is bad. Need 90 wishes to get a 5 star and still not guaranteed a featured character. The in game currency also to expensive to buy, so automatically you need a lot of money to get character. I am stupid enough to buy it and now my money is contributing the game development. But the company is to greedy. They do not give back to the player that contributing. The event reward is a joke.

I've been playing this game since v1.2. It's used to be one of my fave mobile game, but I feel so much downhills in the newest version. The story has become underwhelming, rushed, and doesn't make senses instead of having good premise. The new characters are boring for me. The chara's design also underwhelming. Raiden's story quest is a joke. New events are repetitive and not fun anymore. It's 1st anni but I don't even feel excited about it. Let's see if I'll change my review for the next update

it has impressive storyline...... if you are a stranger to rpgs anyway. backstory feels a bit lacking, even the ones you get from reading books. latest archon quest exemplifies this, you killed a character with nary a character development within 3 main story chapters unlike the previous antagonist at liyue, seemingly only appearing to just kill herself anyway. the game itself is also very stingy with both rewards, quest drops, and pull rates (what the heck is 0.3% anyway), even its anniversary.

just suggestion from android phone user. implement controller like wireless controller or cable controller, because I used to play this game called sky(months before genshin) and it works without hassle to play with cable controller, I quit that game because the graphic just become worst like jaggy everywhere, the world and the character. controller is a must. I play oceanhorn at android phone using controller and it's more fun that way. by the way I don't even care about your anniversary reward

I was rating this game 5 stars, but now down to 2 stars because : 1. Nothing to do (even spiral abyss reseted after 2 weeks now become something like an erand) 2. Daily quest with really just like that reward (I have reached the highest world level, why there's no more reward from daily ? It's stuck like lower world level) 3. Anniv seems lack luster. I have been playing a year with almost no daily skipped (even when I sick, I asked my friends to do the dailies) and on the anniv what I got ? 10 pulls like 1.3 ? I think 1.3 have better reward than the anniv. heck, your maintenance compensation is better than anniv reward (because they somewhat non existence) How can you be like this genshin ? you started as the best F2P game I have ever play and flop so hard on you own anniv ? Remember when you reach total players ? Remember when you get your achievement as best game on playstore and app store ? Remember you already got 1B USD on your first 6 months or so ? Why it got so hard for you to give anything on your own anniversary ? You got so big yet you give so small

My best game so far with Arknights, i play both games from the first day launch. Top up alot And never miss a single day doing the same daily etc... Good character desain, good music soundtrack, good gameplay. But.. It feels like the game didnt appreciated the player. I know theres a lot of toxic player in the community. But.. the anv just dont feel rights. Its just feel like a normal event other than 1 year anv. I really hope they give us the community a feed back. Not just silence. ü•≤

Good game, good graphics designer & illustrator, but bad developer. This game still have lot issues such suddenly reconnecting when domain or spiral abyss it make player need to start over again, line signal never got green its always yellow. We got delay when we try take a drop

This game has nice graphics, nice combat systems, this game requires a lot of time to be spent to fully experience the current content. The game has an energy based system in which you can farm items that enhances the strength of your characters, you could pay for in game currency to get more energy but those in game currency should just be spent on gambling to get more characters. In game currency could be farmed but it's sometimes bot enough to get the character that you want.Worth trying out.

The 1st anniversary rewards are horrible, not because it lacks the quantity. But because it lacks the exclusivity. Anyway, that's not all that needs to be fixed. Uh, do you remember that hangout events exists? Yeah can we get more of those? Or maybe more character story quests that focuses more on the character rather than the world of Teyvat. Also, can we do something about filler patches? Make events that are interesting and fun like the 1.4 minigames not events like the seelie event. Thanks.

The game is very nice at the start! Smooth animations and great story! I loveee the atmosphere and how amazing the character designs aren But after awhile it ends up super repetitive and boring? They literally just have the same character archetypes just in different regions. And besides that, the animation just got really jank? Not to mention the company's greed. It's very hard to accumulate in-game currency when you're in the end game. Plus the unclear tutorials at the start Please fix these

The game is breathtaking for its exploration. I still remembered myself looting everything in front of my eyes when i just started this game. And even now after a year playing, I'm still amazed by the details on the world within. Unfortunately i feel the management is a bit stingy in their rewards and gacha system, so that's 1 star loss there.

Very underwhelming and greedy company. 1.There are bugs everywhere, They even cant fix it properly 2. performance drop every updates, 3. no interesting event anymore, they just made event with previous skin event from previous versions lol, 4. they made promises to players that "promises" later became "hallucinations" which is never happened lol 5. Characters design became more and more copy paste skills, 6. Monsters in game became more and more buff while the characters got debuff 7. Etc

It's become bored, I play because of the characters (design,skill,and useful), now everything is broken or trash i don't care with anything else, fix the character or else many players like me will stop, i've seen many of my friends stop playing because of this. And the new Update is not worth my time.

i've been playing since it release until now, everything was flawless until you reach until ar55 and bored not so much to do because all map and chest 100%, the only thing i can do now is killing monster, spend resin, and daily route artifact, maybe you should make auction system where player can trade good artifact with mora or something, so people will do more daily kill monster

4 Star For Gameplay! Is Fun, The Team Mechanic, Switching Mechanic, But no end and Daily Game That is not Lock by Resin 5 Star For Music! 5* for open world. 2.5* it is hard to play in mobile phone. 1* for gacha rate 5 times in row got 1 4*. Forget to get 5*, even to get multiple 4* is very difficult. Got pity reward?
