I love this game, this game is so good, the animation, the story, the gameplay. But really, their ignorance against their own anniversary and the community, its the worst. I've waited for version 2.2 livestream, incase Mihoyo want to make the event in version 2.2, but turns out there is nothing, nothing at All. They dont even bother to make even a little anniversary event, there is nothing at all, only 10 IF that you can even get by simply playing for a few days. I'm very dissapointed.

good grapchis. story is ok but there are some story a bit weird, some story always viewing about liyue, this is a bit weird if i said, u must make it balance.. my suggest is try to make story in another nation without liyue. maybe will make players see this game in other side at looking. and please for future make more content.. now im very dissapointed as end game player.. i just login, do daily, spend resin and then exit game. and its just take 30min for me to do that... please hear my voices!

Update 8/10/21: after their anniversary mess, i lost interest in playing this game. I played cook*e r*n kingd*m & it was sooo easy to earn coin-materials-crystal, very generous with prizes & rewards too. Then when i get back playing genshin, it was just too huge of a gap; in genshin you have to grind HARD just to earn a small amount of chara lvl.up material. Everyhing is designed to require you to spend money to make it easier, in every single aspect

first of all, the gameplay is quite good, the visual is stunning, but i got some issue with genshin 1. the latter's questline felt so rushed, which is very disappointing for lore freak like i am 2. more and more enemies/bosses just straight up annoying to deal with (winged slimes, electro oceanid, signora) 3. for a player that played from the start it started to get boring to play, no endgame but grinding for artefacts and spiral abyss

The story is very good. The characters are really unique and have a really nice personality. But the end game content is very lacking, even after a year of complaining the only late game thing there is, it's only the spiral abyss, after that there's nothing more to it. The artifact system is kinda stupid, because of the capped resin system. Still, it's a pretty solid game.

I cant reccomend this to anyone for now, the games rely on 0.6 gacha chance to get 5 stars, and the cost is absurd. Not to mention sticking 1 year is not rewarding enough, they cant appericiate playerbase, im sad. Last time i rate 1 stars due to anger, ill make it 3 to be fair for them. I might change it again if genshin is getting better by time.

1. This game have gacha system for characters, weapons. They're not actually that bad if you're a dolphin, harder for f2p 2. Story is quite good, until you went to Inazuma. There are 3 places, Inazuma is third. 3. Grinding artifacts for your characters is VERY HARD. It has the shittiest RNG. 4. Gameplay so far is fun, but it's starting to get boring. So far everything was great, until they unlocked Inazuma on somewhere this year (2021).

Losing lottery gives some mora you could farm in a week. Winning lottery gives you 5 dollars. That's they're big anniv finish. Arknights anniversary is straight up 30ish pulls, half to pity. They kept shoving down web events onto you. This game just feels like an ARG. Daily grind, exit, daily grind, Mihoyo gave new web event, weekly abyss sweep, exit. The game is fun, but it's so spread out and you need to keep grinding. RPG is known for grinds, but I thought the G stands for Game, not Grind.

at first this game was really fun, the story is good and also the characters are great. but then when Inazuma came it just went downhill. lately, i started to feel burnout bcs how dull and boring the quest felt. i first gave it a 5* but now i give it a 4*. i'm kinda close to just uninstalling the game bcs of the burntout. i feel like mihoyo is kinda rushing to give the player more contents and that kinda make the story not as amazing as before. could be better

Played in Q3 2021, and realized new *5 carry heroes are weak, especially on 2.0 and 2.1, I heard one of them become worst hero in the game. Top 3 heroes are from 2020 up until now they NEVER make equal power like them, makes me think twice to spend to this game anymore. if somewhat mihoyo release new strong equal heroes or rebalance heroes to change the Top 3 power level. I will really apprecate it. (rerun does not count)

Used to really love this game. The lore, characters, settings, and music is amazing. But with how rushed the last archon quest is, how dirty the story did on kokomi for not showing her strategic side at all, how the company treat the players in the anniversary, the nonsense on the moonchase charms being untradeable for few rewards, I feel very disappointed.

Overall Nice Performances. Love the game, character development, adventure and story. Also very addictive with the coop feature. But for low end devices it lags a lot and there are still minor bugs ruining the game experience. I know the devs are working hard on how to patch them and all. especially with updates every few weeks. (Game could also be very stressful and boring once you get to the point where the quests are all finished and all you have to do is waste resin and grind for materials)

I think highly of mihoyo but the team developing this genshin impact is really bad. They asking feedback every update but no answer.no endgame content. Repeat filler content and mini games. The game is fun but i suggest new player think before u start to top up. The stronger u get and the faster u rush the faster it gets dry

The game itself is very fun to play, I love the earlier characters, but the latest updates have really bad storylines (to a point that it made the new characters kind of lackluster) and I just can't seem to get as into it as I previously did.. Still hoping for the best, maybe the next patches will be better.. ;w;

For free to play game in mobile this is the best, have great music and gameplay, BUT it need internet continously and very unnecessary, i always play single player and it affect my gameplay (like lagging), please tune down the needed of the internet connection, Thank you. (I give review 1 star too make you notice my problem i had and thank you for your attention.)

Dont delete my commentüòÇ. Alright here, ill write a good one, this game is nice and its not fully pay to win, paying in this game is just basically "speeding up" your progress on getting new characters and upgrading. You can actually get any characters if you grind, of course it'll take time but even if you miss the limited banner you can wait next year or smth for rerun. This game's gacha system is pretty fair, too. But yes, it gets pretty boring when you're halfway which is level 30+.

Edit: one year later and i feel really sad about how the game just stop listening to the playerbase. The effort to gain ratio is just not worth it. I put in so much time and energy to the game but i get barely anything in return, it's quite disappointing. And now that anniversary is here, i could compare to other titles or games of the same types anywhere (even the ones from the same company) and they would be more caring and generous to the players. I just really hope they would listen.
The game is amazing, and the art and design are stunning. However I don't like how they manage event rewards by giving players worst reward possible for free publicity

The game is actually pretty good but on end game your gaming experince become somekind of dull routinities. There are no more rewards you can get and the game become boring. The community was hoping that the anniversary will be a big event but we were wrong, the anniversary isn't even that great. Not to mention that they make us collect expiring items that give us nothing and can't be traded for anything else, I feel disapointed with the way they trick the event.
replyContent: We'd like to thank all Travelers for your continued support and love of Genshin Impact! We will continue to provide you with more high-quality game content. If Travelers encounter problems during their adventures, please don't hesitate to contact us via the in-game feedback channel. Your gaming experience and suggestions are always important to us.

content: 10 minute grind a day game because lack of endgame content. But u have to grind because RNG in artifact is absolute trash. Same with the gacha rate, u have to count on the pity system because the chance is ridiculously low. Even anniversary rewards have some kind of gacha, not everyone get it. 100k mora dont count as a reward, its hardly enough to level up your talent. The music's great, but the developer is big on censorship. They already deleted reviews like this countless times.

It's heavy gacha game. Almost everything inside the game is gacha. Character, Weapon, Artefact (item to make your character stronger). Drop n Upgrade Gacha, Events Gacha for extrem low rewards which is not enough for 1 character/weapon Gacha. The feedback from Players will not be heard, a lot of bugs for around 3-6 months ago but they only fix the minor bug. The marketing team is trash, I kinda feels bad for the developer team.

This game is seriously addictive, but the things that I don't like is that this game took so much space. But I'm still rating this a 5 star game just because this game has good graphics, great story lines, and it's interesting. /edit i change my mind.)

The game is good. But the devs rarely listen to the community, right now i just want to say to pls not making us download all the characters voice-over, i had to download 2 gb data just for japanese voice over, most of the playable characters in genshin are limited so it's not a good thing that all the voice over is downloaded becuz it's making us players suffer from downloading it. I might have to delete most of my games for genshin. Rn my genshin is 17 gb and probably delete some used cutscene

Repetitive and has no end game content. This game requires you to buy a lot of crystals to gain more characters. The gambling system in this game is predatory. Not gonna buy a single genesis crystal or welkin from this greedy company.
So I get this thing where I log in and go to enter and its says the maintenence times, so I hit confirm, then the audio cuts out, and it kicks me out. This is after the last update

They could fix the anniversary but they didn't the story I don't really pay attention to but genshin needs to add more content and many things like It were a better game if things werent rushed and the character design are really cute and sometime hot but raiden story quest has to be the most jokes thing ever but you really need to fix and do better in my opinion

Greedy asf@ck! At first it's great but eventually you'll really need to shed money to make it interesting again. Like only 0.0005% you'll get a chance to get a 5 star hero or even a decent hero. Keep your players happy, just give them good heroes or option to buy thier favorite hero. Why do you need to make it hard for players? I'm telling you this will not last long unless you guys change how you treat the majority of us casual players. So disappointing. üëéüèª

I like genshin impact because of their story fantasy the art scenery is so amazing and the music is too intense and calmed, it defense where your location the music is change I love it.When you start the game you become addicted to it, you never know what is the time. Overall I recommended to all try it, it is fun.10 out of 10 . Perfect for all ages.

High quality graphics games always have a place in my smartphone. Gigantic open world. Original exciting story like you never heard before. Jaw dropping scenery. And the soundtracks, its so memorable. Keep up the good work. This game already became my favorite. Why 1 star? Because this game didn't care about most players, only care to those players who's pay the most and to those streamers who's give free ads.

For new players this game is 5 stars because there is so much content to do from main story to character quests. However for those like myself who have been playing since day one it is a 1 star as there is little to no content to do. Even when there are updates, the new content is minimal and are reskins of previous patches. If the company speeds up content roll out it, I would increase my rating. It seems like they are intentionally slowing the rollout to make more money from fans.

This game really brings me alot of joy, yes sometimes the rewards for things are a little underwhelming, but as a f2p I don't really like complaining. The visuals are amazing, sometimes a little glitchy, I love the choices of characters too. How they're all different and all have a part in the story line. Overall a great game üíï

Genshin is wonderful, honestly there isn't much else to say! It takes an eternity to load when updating or first starting out, but that's just because it's such a high quality game! I've had two accounts at this point and enjoy the game throughly, very fun! I love exploring, finding new quests, cooking, and playing with friends, overall five stars! (b ·µî‚ñΩ·µî)b

Similar to Zelda, Breathe of the Wild. Open world and scenery is breathtaking. There are lag and sync issues when playing in co-op for the host. Daily tasks can be redundant. Relay puzzles can be frustrating; half of them require YouTube help. Overall, I've been playing since it was released. It's a lot of fun. Hopefully devs will be more generous with primogems. 2 per common chest and 5 per precious chests is kinda sad, especially when a spawn is 160; and it took me forever to find the chest
Please be better for the future implementation ingame,. I love the play style, story, even the npc is sometimes funny. Hope u guys learn from the past.

The game is great, with awesome visuals, and story telling. It's just now consuming to much memory on my mobile to update. I fear I won't be able to play it anymore because of how much memory data it's consuming

I wasn't aware it was available on PC when I began, so I started on mobile. I love the open world exploration! I wish multi-player wasn't so pushed in this game, it makes it hard to participate in events when they require you to play with others and you have no friends that play. I'm also a huge fan of the fact that diving under the water isn't a thing, I have a horrible time playing games where that's a required thing for missions. Very fun! #BringBackXiao #ReRuns

Great game, it has a lot of content. although, when it comes to endgame replayable content the game can get rather dry, every day it's the same routine: Farm domains for artifacts, daily comms and spiral abyss. that aside i believe the game provides an awesome experience especially to the new player, story is great (imo at least), character and enviroment design is top notch and the gameplay is also fairly fun. overall a great game despite having quite a few flaws.

I would love to give this game 5 stars but sadly I must say, the rewards are disappointing. They mostly give you coins, witch is fine for the first few times, but when it's almost every reward it's very disappointing. I would love not to spend money on the game but due of this I spend alot of money. PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASE, PLEASEEEE make the rewards much better!!!!

This game have amazing story, beautiful art & music, interesting gameplay, the game map is so vast and diverse, and the content is enough to keep you playing for a month or two. That being said it is far from being perfect. The gacha rate is horrible to said the least, resin system is annoying, and farming for artifacts is the worst thing in this game. The developer looks like they never listen nor appreciate their player base whatsoever, the anniversary fiasco is just one example out of some.

I think it is a good game and all but I just dont like how much GB it uses and I want be able to play a lot cause my phone is not much to carry a lot of GB and the game gets boring some time and if I cant play due to gb then I did everything for nothing

For the beginning it's the best game with amazing view and amazing content,but in the end it's become boring without new content and repetitive content every day, and it's become more worst with the gacha

Great game with a great story. Main issues I have is it only has one endgame game mode right now, no daily login and weekly bosses need to have the resin cost removed. other then that it's probably the best open world game on mobile.

I've been seing lots of bad reviews for this game but I personally love this game, I've been playing this game for around 3-4 months without missing a single day. I enjoyed playing this game with my friends and I'm in love the storyline and the character designs. I gave 4 stars because the lack of end game content, that's my problem for now. For people who have finished the story, they would have to wait for the next update to continue the storyline. But, it does not bother me that much to wait.

The game is so much fun, the graphics are amazing, the characters are cute, the gameplay music is astonishing, i just wish that their would be better/more rewards and more attention to the fanbase from the developers.
This game had become a gamble rather than a free to play its became a bit more greedy but the gameplay is still a bit enjoyable except if you're at the end game
This game have improved , but the primogems are the problem there. Players like me who plays it for free .have to do more work.

Good game play, horroble PR, very expensive gatcha game, and you can't make purchases through Google Play if you started on console. Even if you played since launch, end game comes quick and is boring but a grind you spend a month on for one decent artifact out of the 5 you need per character.
Good game but players are not rewarded enough for their commitment in this game. Keqing, as of now, is just as good as a 4 star character, please pay attention on the character and buff her please.

Honestly, the prices for in game purchase are kinda high, which means if you do not have lots of money, you might not be able to buy good stuff. I'd love to see the prices going down so everyone get a chance to get nice things.

Honestly I don't care about the anniversary reward that much.. Imo genshin anniversary made me realize time flies so fast its so nostalgic remembering the time I played genshin on 1.0 all the exploration I've done or all your players have done I'm in love with this game mihoyo!! There's just one thing you need to do which is listen to your community more.. Just like the old times haha the more I remember it the more I feel sad seeing people just caring for rewards and not enjoying the game. :)

It's fun in the beginning. But the further you get the less there is to do. The rewards are so lackluster. You work hard to level up but the reward is unreasonably wrong. The weapon and character banner is even separated, which you need more primogems or fates for you to get the weapon or character you desire. It's hard to be a free to play in this game. You can't enjoy this game if you're just a free to play. What's there to enjoy? Grinding?

Gameplay is fun and addictive, and there's tons to explore in the game. The lack of endgame content is a dissapointment though, and co-op is also lacking. Characters are fun to play and build on and generally have cool designs. Minus points for greed, this can be mad expensive if you want to collect characters. My girlfriend and I still play, quite often too. We both luck'd out with a 5-star right away to use in our parties. A have the feeling I'm going to hit a content wall soon though..
An amazing game, only 4 stars because how little primos are gifted as rewards despite players spending so much money on the game, it's a shame. However this doesn't deter me from playing!

Open World, Adventure, Action, Gatcha, Co-op, Waifus and Husbandos. A very solid game in terms of gameplay, stunning graphics and views, fun characters to mix and match. Characters have a pretty decent drop rate especially on banners. The game is updated regularly and new events come monthly. The community is in a Love/Hate relationship with the devs because they listen when there are needed fixes/additions to how the game is played but ignore the wants and needs of the player base in Rewards...

It's good from the FIVE MINUTES I played. This app took a day to download, not to mention I'm writing this while it's updating AGAIN. The updates are required as far as I know so I'm getting a bit aggravated. The art is amazing and I would really like to play it so I hope it starts working soon. Edit: I'm deleting this app. I would love to play it but this isn't worth my time.

Good game but character progress is slow. The game has great character designs and beautiful landscapes. However, it has multiple systems in place to hinder progressing your characters. The game is worth trying because early game exploration and story is excellent but don't put money in unless you don't mind grinding and jumping through endless hoops for months to level up characters.

Amazing game.Might be rough around the edges for mobile users, but as long as you have a decent phone it should run like butter. The game is very unique and extremely high quality, no game like it exists currently. The game is super fun and the characters and story are god tier. It suffers from a lack luster endgame and dry seasons of content before every update. The game can feel very unbalanced and no changes are being made. The gacha system is predatory so I recommend not spending any money.

Game is beutiful, but the things you could do is very limited, the rewads for exploring is as good as trash, the devs are very stingy on giving out anything worth while. Its a very grindy game that limits your grinding time (you will know what that means in-game) none the less is a good free to play game.

The total experience is really enjoyable, the art style is very pleasing, the story is one of the best out there and I hope that it won't degrade at some point, the events are really enjoyable but it as a whole the daily gameplay for endgame players are kind of boring due to lack of content I think it still has a lot of room for improvement. The gacha system also has a ton of room for improvement and the daily comms too. The dev and community relationship is really not that great in my opinion.

It started out as a really pleasant game, but the recent updates seem to cause more lags for older devices that meets minimum specs that it has affected overall satisfaction. Glad to see 2FA is finally addressed to, but there are still a lot more to work on, especially on issues like the drop in story writing quality.
replyContent: We are sad to hear you are experiencing these issues. We would love to help! Please contact our cs team at genshin_cs@mihoyo.com so that we may have you back up and running as soon as possible.

content: I live this game, the graphics are great, tje game play is fun, and not laggy. the only thing is the amount of data it takes, i am complaining because it took me around 2 hours to first load the game. anyway good game. i recommed that while its loading just watch something else and wait.
i love this game but it's just too unfair on the wishes. I know it's like a loot box but please give us something better at least.
It's a fun game but once you've done everything it gets boring just waiting for updates, other then that, if you like gachs games and a lot of grinding this is the game for you.

It's a super beautiful game with super nice graphics the only thing that's making me rate it 3 stars is the cut scenes they keep on chopping please fix that it is really ruining the experience and potential of the game

it's a really nice game. beautiful graphics and all but i was really dissapointed with the co op system. like you couldn't play with friends who are in different servers. at least you could use a warning before giving the player the option to choose the server? like "heyy just a reminder that you can't play with players in different servers in co op mode," and other than that, the price for the gems are too expensive. the double reset won't do anything long term

This is a nice game, I already play this for a few months now, but I don't recommend to download this game on the old phones since they have low storage, but, those who can't download this game, I would love to tell you this is a wonderful game. Though this requires good internet to play and you always reconnect if you have bad internet, but it is still a fun game

This is my honest review, this game is fine for me. Many people complain about the anniversary reward but bro... They have been generous enough about the gift reward and about the content drough endgame, you can still participate in many events that renewed if the previous one has ended so its not a content drought game. Yes maybe all you can do is just do daily comission and spend resin everyday but imagine this game is still in developement and its very promissing!

Boring as you progress, nothing much to do, stingy devs, false marketing, cant have good characters or weapons if not spending money, even spending money not guaranteed. Limited resources such as resin, and everything needs resins !
There's no end game content. Once you get 36 stars in abyss, there's nothing to do. Add that to the expensive gacha and it's not a very great experience. The anniversary fiasco didn't help.

Great open world game. But lack of direction and road map has caused many to burn out. Beginning content is fun and exciting. Once you complete teams end game becomes nonexistent. Becomes typical grinding game with gacha to get 5* characters and weapons.

The graphics are amazing! It takes up quite a bit of space, but my phone doesn't have a problem with that. The game itself is very entertaining and a lot of it is a dice roll, which I find fun. 10/10, would recommend to anyone looking for a way to entertain themselves during this Covid period! Happy playing!

This is a 5 star game for me, and one of my favorite games period. With a beautiful world to explore, a fascinating story, and so many very well written characters to meet, it's been such a fun year of playing. It can get a little grind-y, and there isn't a ton of endgame content yet. Aside from that it's honestly a great experience if you don't mind investing a little time. But there is a terrible lack of communication, and ignoring major issues while fixing ones that feel a lot less important.

RNG everywhere. RNG to get characters and weapons is one thing and it is fine. But the ridiculous RNG in getting artifacts and also RNG in leveling up those artifacts are insanely rigged. Unless you pay to do resin refreshes that allows you to do more gacha for said artifacts. Otherwise, this game would have been deserving of 4 or even 5 star rating.

love, love, LOVE this game, its mechanics, graphics, designs characters and more. the only real true complaint i have is that it takes up too much storage and is very laggy. i struggle to make space EVERY single update, mind you i dont have anything else downloaded but social media. this makes it rlly difficult to enjoy the game.. cuz well, i cant rlly play it most of the time. pls somehow reduce the size for ppl like me!

This game may not be the best when it comes to fulfilling the playerbase's expectation..hell, they don't even communicate to address the core problems of the game through their official social media accounts. However, aside from the lack of communication, this game is still a solid game. The combat system, story, and characters are all wonderfully well-written. Don't let the low review determine if this game is one of those bad rip-offs. Although the anniversary wasbad, there's always next year.

It's a gacha game, but there's a full game supplied for free. Better writing, better world building, better character design. Pretty much the only downside is that the community is a bunch of whiners who throw hissy fits at the tiniest opportunity, but you don't need to engage with them to play.

Not a big player of rpg game and only had maybe 3-4 hours in the game. Pretty fun to play, lookin forward to the story. EDIT: I've played the game for almost a year now. My focus has changed from playing the story to just trying to get my favourite characters and upgrading. This in itself isn't all that bad, but it does get boring after you have accomplished that and new contents is not released yet. Not to mention you can spend A LOT just to get the characters and weapons and to upgrade them!

The music and art are 10/10, but the lack of endgame content and communication between mihoyo and players is shockingly bad. They have been getting more and more greedy, ignore our requests to fix the resin cap or the resin recharge rate, and there have been many unfulfilled promises to us. We want to recieve road maps and updates on what is planned for the future, its really disappointing that a game with such immense potential is let down by the marketing team and customer support.
lackluster rewards, too many bugs, artifacts are too RNG-based and past a certain point, there's nothing else to do.

The only reason this game gets 3 stars is because I don't want honkai impact to suffer too. If you hate genshin, and only being able to run around in the open world with very miniscule means to leveling up, just switch to honkai.

The game is amazing and top tier. it would be great if they could add skins for charecters , maybe mounts for higer level adventurers. Overall the game is a bliss.... But the developers need to communicate and address the actual issues with the game.

After playing for 7 months, now i think i can give 5 stars from 2 stars. everything seemed to be changes and getting better over time. But please improve multiplayer system, such as making clan/guild system, pvp arena, clan/guild wars and last but not least stall or market system to trade something between players, to make the game more enjoyable. Good Luck

I won't deny, this is actually a really great game. But only at the beginning. Don't know why, but it seems there are a lot of things in this game that just doesn't work that well and even if the whole community gave their voices and asked for the problems to be solved, nothing seems to happen. No wonder people are burnt out, even I myself who had been playing since day 1 felt like I'm logging in just to find myself with nothing to enjoy and be happy about anymore...

Genshin is a game with great potential and talented devs hindered entirely by greedy higher-ups. Endgame is an utter joke and permanent content is so trivial that building new units is meaningless outside of full clearing Abyss, which you only do twice a month for bad rewards. Artifact grinding is also a time sink and disincentivises pulling new units. Top tier art and lore across the board though

Good game, it's been a year im playing this game. Late game is kinda boring there isnt much to do beside min-maxing artifact for spiral abyss. Weapon banner is unforgiving for f2p. hope they implement better system on that one.

Please make beidou and shogun synergy work. Please make kokomi's E skill able to be repositioned like Oz Please improve Yoimiya targetting Please fix klee spark flower ICD. The so called temporary fix you made has been permanent with no updates. Please give better artifact rates for weekly bosses

One of the best games I have ever played. ‚ù§ Sadly, it feels like PayToWin, as wishes are very expensive Primogem-wise, and Primogems are awfully difficult to get unless you do a lot of quests, which can take hours. A great mechanic, though, is that you have a Pity (50/50) Mechanic, where if you get a 5-Star on a banner that you don't want, the next 5-Star is definitely the secondary one. Great logic :) Please make the game better for FreeToPlay players, Mihoyo! I look forward to more Genshin. :)
I LOVE THE GAME OVERALL! But the only problem was that it often bugs and glitches. And its so hard to do quests when they don't give very specific directions.

Alright hello! So this game is really nice and free too. Of course with gacha, there's farming. At least the farming is less repetitive since you can move and have diff outcomes in terms of success. But still some heavy farming. Mihoyo needs to pay more attention to this game because I KNOW there should be more content for more casual gaming that other games have. But I am still happy with the memes and story. Be mature and give constructive criticism guys :) Mihoyo can still do better though!

I've played this game for over a year. It was fun at first. I could play for hours and hours a day without getting bored. Now I can barely play for 15-30 mins. I get on, collect my welkin, and maybe spend my resin if I feel motivated enough. Lovable characters, and beautiful atmosphere. Sadly those things don't make up for the lack of end game content and story. Like with most gacha games, the company isn't exactly generous. I wish I could enjoy this game again, but sadly I cannot.

I love playing this game. It has good gameplay, has a great progressive story and is very fun to play with friends. But, the company and devs just don't bother listening to players queries/concerns and despite earning millions or billions they aren't willing to make the community happy during the anniversary, which I feel sad about as a gacha gamer.

This is the best MMORPG that I've ever played. From graphics to the world itself. So interesting in many ways. The characters are well built, with their interesting passives and own uniqueness. All have its own differences that I can't really compare between 2. The world is very vast, makes me worried how you will accommodate w/the storage problem for mobile users. I guess that's what's ur supposed to be working on. All in all, you all done a splendid job!

i love the lore and the characters, but please fix the signora and dvalin glitch on mobile...i cant even fight them both to continue the story i literally had to ask my cousin to fight them on his pc for this..its so annoying. if this is a mobile game, make it like one. not everyone is rich enough to buy a laptop. thank u

Very good game, have been playing for months although there is not much to do once you catch up with the story, more daily things to do would be nice (serenitea pot was a great move in this direction)

I honestly love this game the characters are cute and the story is nice same with game play, but wishes and gifts are really bad, I mean sometimes they're good but not alot, I would recommend this game to anyone but tell them to get ready for frustration when it comes to wishing and disappointment when getting presents.

Overall it's a good game, both their main story and side story were satisfying and interesting, and its adventurous to explore different places to do tasks or just idly go around is its' charm. It's just the gacha system is kinda bad cuz it has low probability, but not to p2w players that could get way better characters and weapons. Not to mention their anniversary celebration didn't as generous as other gacha games. But I'm looking forward for some improvement, Mihoyo. Keep up the good work.

The game is great. Also i think the devs isn't that bad. Story is hit and miss. Character design is great. Every character have their own potential. The game is very suited for players that only play about 1-3 hours a day. Or just small refreshing after work BUT, BEWARE THIS GAME DOESN'T SUIT FOR PLAYER THAT PLAY 5 OR MORE HOURS A DAY The content won't be enough for you. Also. Don't mind those 1 star review just because "rewards" most of them is just bandwagon.

Amazing, the story is so fun and the characters too the originality everything even the name itself sounds majestic after you play for a few months! I feel like 2/3 parts of my brain carry information about this game and it's story along with every character's story that I know of.. even around 60 playable characters, just amazing. My favorite game, I have always loved games in which you explore wild life and also that are exiting and challenging, can't believe I love it more than Zelda BOTW.

Overall a good game, besides the fact that after you finished all the quests, you've got nothing to do except the daily commissions. Which could easily be solved by making the resin replenish more quickly, or permanently add daily logins that could reward players with resin. And I'm not going to talk about the gacha since that would decrease the star review.

It's a wonderfull game with lots of adventures. But I rate it 4* because I just don't really like a few characters in this game. But it's a free game and really easy to play. I hope miHoYo will creat more interesting characters.

Great Game, no other game current can compare to it. That being said the game has many bugs and not functioning aspects that need to be addressed by the creators . When they start doing those fixes only then i will rate this game a 5 star.

Exceptional stories and graphics. Every characters have different gameplays. Lots of weapons and artificacts to collect. Stories of each characters are special and unique. Vast world map to explore. I enjoy playing this game. Pity to those who thinks they can put down a great game by giving low rating. What a shameful act. This game deserves a high merit.

Game itself is excellent in terms of graphics, VAs, script and music but in terms of game mechanics like in abyss, skill interaction of characters, and i-frames is a total dogshit. Also the company itself doesnt communicate with the community which is sooo annoying. They'll just send you primogems in your mail just to stfu and play the game. Disgusting

Game production is very intricate and beautiful. Only concerns are the gacha rates, unfriendliness towards f2p and how they've worsened weapon gacha guarantee. They're slowly adding more features so I'm hoping the game will make it less harder to gain primogems.

The game itself is amazing it is fun and I never have nothing to do the devs are getting a lot of hate because of the anniversary rewards and I understand why. The game does have a lot of things that need to be fixed but I still think it's a great game. The only wards I have towards the devs is that they should communicate more with the community.
I love this game. I love stories in game. Perfect visual. But sometimes it's hard when co-op.
Absolutely beautiful, only minor bugs that I'm confident will be fixed soon. The biggest one being that they need to let me pet the dog in town. Why have a dog if we can't pet it?

Thank you Mihoyo for making such a beautiful game. The game is very very unique. I really wished I started the game very early to see the Lanter rite festival. The scenery's are breathtaking, the story's are well written, the characters are unique and the puzzles are fun. Take your time in making the other nations. I wish that the old community comes back. MIHOYO PLEASE LET ME WITH THE 50/50 FOR CHILDE'S BANNER <3333

As a player from D1, I'm disappointed in how MHY handles situations with community communication. I love the game but it's been a type of reoccurring problem for awhile, tho I can see a bit of progress. I know MHY and the game can do better with being transparent by giving timelines and make us have more incentive to continue playing other than waiting for new events. My will to play has decreased because everything feels like a chore for primos but I have hope because I love the chars and story

I started in February and only recently started to get bored in September so there's actually a pretty good amount of content to go through and there's usually new events every month or so to try too. You do get bored but the characters keep me coming back.

After version 2.0, i was realized if this game manifestation story and event based on version because it needs hard implementation. But, i was feel lack of playing in samsung galaxy A21s and graphical disturb me when battle with boss. Maybe you should update in this device

Rewards for higher ARs should be better. After a certain point, the daily quests and other quests start to seem like chores. With the increase un the number of bossesand domains, shouldn't the total resin per day also increase? There should be better compensation for when you get a C6ed character especially if its a 5*. I don't want to wait another 90 wishes to get a character while i only get 5 wishes as compensation. The game is fun in the early stages, could be made fun for later too.

Good game. Wish there was better camera control, especially for mobile users. I keep getting my camera plunged in to the grass whenever I get hit in combat and the sensitivity to pull the camera back to normal is such a hassle especially if ur trying to stay alive pressing other buttons.

This is the stingiest gacha game i have ever played with 0.6% ssr rate it's worse than FGO. So if you're f2p prepare for gacha salt. I do love the world and voice talent involved. Mechanically it's much more engaging than many other mmos. The recent characters and gameplay announcements made me reconsider my rating, so there. Actively waiting for Itto, Thoma and Gorou

Such a great game! This game deserves more 5 star reviews, sadly the fandom (even those who doesn't even play it) are rating it as 1 star bcuz of the anniversary rewards. I'm also disappointed abt it but the fandom took it too far. I hope those toxic players quit and never play Genshin again. They're making the game bad. Keep it up Mihoyo!!! This game and the company deserves more appreciation and love!! Also Qiqi and Thoma come home pleaseeee! We love you Mihoyo!

this game is so addicting (in a good way) it helps my stress and also make me more stress cus the artifacts grind is hell... but i still enjoy it tho, i love the scenery and bgm, cool story, pretty characters, etc. yea, i wish this game have more improvement either in the gameplay or in other aspects. hope my device is strong enough to go on with this game :'D thanks genshin & mihoyo! wish u all the best ig

I knowingly started amidst all the controversy, just to see if the initial hype and later collective disappointment were justified. The game is overall "good", but it's nothing outer worldly. I wish the grinding wasn't as extensive to level up a character. The open world and exploring mechanics are quite good

I LOVE this game the graphic are amazing the storyline is so much fun and the wishing ect is nerve wracking but in a good way! I've been playing with my friends in Co-op and we've really bonded because of it. Totally recommend!

Genshin Impact is the mobile game I have always wanted and while not perfect, it is as close as I will likely ever see under the current rapacious monetization system that is ruining gaming for all but the most privileged and most stupid. In fact, were it not for the gacha mechanics of the game I would give it five of five stars. That said, Genshin Impact is undoubtedly the most satisfying mobile game currently available. I am certainly addicted. You would have to be a pretty bitter pill to not

Probably the best free mobile app game out there. You don't have to pay anything to play. Paying is totally optional and is up to you (Many of things are very affordable. If you plan to invest, make sure to remember that you can only purchase with the same device type you created your account). This game is also co-op(is crossover co-op mobile/PC and consoles are compatible to play together). I have a lot of fun with the mpnthy events and Dailey quests.

This game is too good to be a free game. But some players gave bad ratings because they thought the anniversary rewards were not enough, demanding miHoYo to give a free 5*. But if you try to see from the developer's point of view, if one of the first anniversary rewards is a 5*, then the players will demand more greater rewards for the next anniversaries. I may not be paid to say this but I still want to share my opinion and I am not saying miHoYo is fair either, for ignoring players' feedbacks.

Yes, the anniversary rewards were not much. But after that they gave us more ten pulls, 1 free glider and 2 fragile resin. That was enough. But recently, in the 2.1 version the story quest was boring.

Been a year when this game became part of my everyday life. And it's been a good year because of the co-op's with my friends, the rng's of the artifacts, the everyday and every event grind for gems, and the story that I've been always waiting and looking forward for.

at first I was just curious, then I tried playing it. then I got busy. and then I went back into playing it. there is so much to look forward into. the developers are slowly, but surely delivering the contents that we need and I'm sure all other updates will definitely exceed everyones expectations at some point, I mean, it's just awesome. to other people who plays too fast like, finishing the islands and quests. it may bore them. but for us who just enjoys playing. This is definitely worth it.

Overall the game is good,the characters,the lore,the gameplay,etc you name it,its very well made the dev totally put a lot of efforts in this game,but if this game keeps updating and adding 3gb+ per update most of the players might not be able to play this game becouse big updates,not everyone have a godly phone
The game is fun, beautiful characters, interesting stories as well. Though this is from my perspective, I'd say go on and try it if you're new! :)

I've edited my review from 5 stars to 3. Unfortunately, even though this game is very high quality and has the potential to have an excellent long lasting game, but there's some glaring things to note. The game is need of a slight over haul in terms of content and how their summons work(gacha aspect). They have proven to undervalue their players and have not made content that can be played consistently. Once you reach end game its just a repetitive grind until you arent allowed to grind anymorw

This is actually a good game but plagued with many problems, 1) lack of endgame content making it boring when you reach endgame stage, 2) player don't have control over character progress because artifact status are gacha, 3) can fuel your gambling addiction if you're not careful, 4) lack of communication from management/developer.
The game has a great potential (design, music, gameplay, etc). However, some features and events can be tedious and new characters skill is poorly-designed
Good core game. But has its issues. Artifact (equipment) RNG will make you run the same dungeon every day for a month for something just decent. And the communication from devs could be better.

This is the best mobile game that I ever played. But, high specs phone needed to play this game smoothly. Overall, this game is awesome, and very different with other game. No ranking system, so you don't need to spend much money because you have no one to compete with. Just enjoy the game. RPG players absolutely love this game, because the stories are fascinating, and the nature scenes are awesome with good BGM. I've been played for a year and never get bored on this game.

So chock full of content!! The map is HUGE and yet to grow bigger, and the elemental combat is mad fun to play. My only complaint is the low resin regen and extremely large amount of resin gated content. And the lack of ability to choose which artifact sets to grind. Recently released characters like Yoimiya and Kokomi also have glaring gameplay flaws. Needs more endgame combat content.

File verification error. I'm installing genshin again since we have a new laptop but when it finished downloading and verification begins, an error occurs. Tried downloading it again but it's the same. Cleared resources and reinstalled launcher but it didn't fix it. It's the same with my friend wth is happening? Please fix this, I really like this game. Thanks

Story is good, characters are great, music is amazing, exploration is fun, events great! 5 star rates are bad, artifacts farm is RNG hell, current end game content is lacking. I suggest you play through the first two regions (Monstadt, Liyue) before deciding whether to keep playing.

Never got a single 5 star character I want, which reminded me why I hate gacha games. The game is wayyy to grindy and luck based, if someone has a good amount of free time and likes gambling, sure, have fun, knock yourself out ig.

To be completely honest, this game is amazing! I'm on mobile, so the details aren't that great unlike computer. It's still amazing though! How much work was made into the details of this game and models! It's surprising how this game is free! I've been playing the game since the last zhongli banner, and It will never feel the same again , when you've played for a while. I'm gonna miss when I first started, when I was thrilled to download the app. Such happy memories..where do the days go...?

Animation, Design overall, and music are all superb. But the thing is that, there are multiple things they fail to address and their communication with the community is somehow limited (anniv fiasco, kokomi kit, raiden beidou synergy, etc)
Liked this game very much, easy to play, vast open world, wonderful artwork, beautiful scenery for world design, loved it very much

I have been addicted to this game, its graphics are amazing and the plot too! I dont get why people hate the anniversary rewards, its kind of better than i expected to be honest. Besides that the game is really fun and very addicting! I 100% reccommend downloading
This is saddening looking at the 3.5 stars.. i love this game, and yes the anniversary rewards is a bit meh but hey, the game is not bad...

I use to love this game but, after sometime game is not reward, and asking for money in every step, it's soo bad for players in late game, I have 5$/month subscription for this game still I got nothing to say I m having fun this is the last month I m playing and paying subscription of this game

Game is awesome, but most of the players are dissappointed bcz the terrible communication between the community and the company. There are characters to be fixed for a long time we were complaining bout it over and over but it seems that they arent listening. Also the rewards were unacceptable. But this will be okay the problem is mihoyo doesnt wanna listen the playerbase, dont know why but its bad. Players shouldve been acknowledged and respected.

This game is really cool and have a good potential but I'm still not okay with what happened after one year and how they are listening us tbh. It's not about the rewards, It's about bugs and feedbacks that we are sending to them since a year and they still didn't fix them. They fixed minor bugs like Raiden hallow, but not major bugs....?

Lack of Endgame content. You will be limited to 10-15minutes of meaningful gameplay everyday once you reach a certain level. Wishes/Pulls are expensive. World exploration and gameplay is awesome but once you passed through the honeymoon phase of around 2 weeks everything becomes less rewarding and super grindy. RNG on top of RNG on top of RNG on top of RNG.

The company is known for trying to sweep community concerns under the rug and pretending it doesn't exist. Only once the complaints get loud and disruptive enough do they make some sort of effort to address it, and a lot of times it's so begrudgingly it's almost like an insult and a way for them to get back at the community that has been complaining. MHY should recognize a Chinese approach to community voices does not work when you have a massive international base.

After playing the game for a while it becomes real stale. I haven't pulled since Hu Tao's banner and finished building all mu characters. So without the domain grind, the game barely has any good repeatable content.

Love it so far, I got to ar 40 within a month lol, but ofc its not perfect, imagine a perfect game? Ok so first issue, resin, many people are complaining about this, also artifacts?? I keep getting trash ones everyday, nothing good ://

Good points: Characters, design, story, lore and world is amazing. Fun with friends. Bad points: Gacha, Depends on luck "RNG". Company doesn't listen to their audience's comppains, bug report andsuggestion.TONS of unnecessary dialogue, "for example an hour while skipping". Expensive, you might pay hundreds and not get the character. Unbalanced characters. Rewards sometimes are very disappointing. Too much farming needed. Gameplay gets very boring a lot. Sometimes events are boring + unrewarding.

Best game of its genre. Free-to-play friendly, difficulty is alright and doesn't force you to spend. Too bad a lot of entitled kids review bombed this game because they think they deserve more free rewards.

It's an absolute masterpiece I totally recommend ya'll to play it. It's so fun that ya'll could get addicted to it on the first day!! The only thing is that I am disappointed of the anniversary rewards. Overall ya all should definitely play it :)
it would be great if the monsters and enemies were more varied .. Listen please:D
Pretty fun game at the start I played for months and eventually I got tired of the commissions and such but I would definitely play more if I would play if there was controller setting for mobile.
Update, it's been a year and honestly I love this game. It's sorta nice to f2p and very grindy. Artifact farming is a real pain in the neck. The year rewards we a bust. But it is what it is.
The story and the characters are great however, the pity system makes it really hard to get characters unless you're extremely lucky or spend a lot of money

I really love the quality and sometime if youre a mobile player just like me im pretty sure that it lagging so much its because of my wifi- so i recommend you to play it on pc because the quality makes it more prettier and the story line is very impressive and the charecters are very hot (Àµ Õ°¬∞ Õú ñ Õ°¬∞Àµ)

If the game didn't studder or freeze up all the time and giving you the krappest camera angles when battling an enemy, the game would be freeking awesome. And every time I update the game, it takes me 3 days to play it again. If they could fix these problems, I would highly recommend it.

Probably the 10th time I've had to re-upload my review cause it keeps getting deleted. Very lacking commutation between mihoyo and the players. Complaints are ignored and any problems that new characters might have won't be fixed due to mihoyo's refusal to fix stuff once it's released for some reason. Ignoring those issues it's a lovely and fun game ü•≤
I am rather enjoying this game so far, though would enjoy it more if they added controller support. When they do I will give it 5 stars.

To much update, firsttime i download this game i must download data 13GB and then there's notice that i must update again, well then it says "maintenance" and last i must download 13GB of data again?? How suck this game..

Now that the anniversary rewards have been fixed. We still haven't heard anything of the kfc gliders. They made a statement about them being available for worldwide and telling us how in June or July. But we haven't had the update and haven't heard anything about it since. I think it's a pity that they just ignore topics like these and act like nothings going on

Well still 1 cuz u still haven't made kishi work on android.... Still lot of issues . Still can't change the HUD positioning u stuck with basic and sometimes u tap sprint and the character enters walk mode, or u wanna change to someone else but magically u ult for no reason , mid combat the camera goes into the ground, and sooo on......

I've been playing since 1.0 and personally the game became sort of a chore. On the other hand it is a very good game when you start out. I really recommend it you should definitely try it out. But there will be a time where you'll hit a barrier and have nothing to do. Well that's until mihoyo adds good end game content. Or a new update adding places to explore and more story.
I don't really care about the anniversary rewards but your censorship is too much. It is not possible to string together a basic sentence without it being censored
Really good game, just needs a bit more of end game content, and if only rewards are a bit more rewarding, It is free to play so it's good for everyone. I love the game even with some disappointments
can't switch characters when you are about to get hit and it's ridiculous how much money I spent just to get a good single artefact let alone 4 set, well they are right after all

After this update I got looped, can you fix it? I already update this app, than when open the game it's say update and log in to get 300 primo, press confirm get to Play store again, and no more update. Just play and uninstall button. Press Play, going to the log in, and need to be updated again, than it got repeated. Can Fix it? Thank you

It is a fun and enjoyable game with great experiences and stories that help us ralax the only problem I hav is the space that is consumed to update the game,most of the mobile devices hav their space at 64gigs, so hope u could minimize the amount of space that is consumed other then that is it quiet a breathtaking game

I really love the game. The character design, the story, the open world experience and the fighting mechanics. One part that I find should be improved a lot is the in game rewards, there is not a lot of good things in chests or from events. For example: there should be a higher amount of in game currency (primogems) handed out through rewards for late game or early game users.

I love Genshin, play it everyday. Such amazing graphics, characters are so interesting and each have detail put into them. This is the first game I've liked enough to spend a good amount on. But it seems as though the company doesn't want to give a lot. Not as though I need a lot, but to do what they're doing atm is sad. It's also unfair to those who love the game and just want have things to level up. Idk it's just puts me off in a depressing way. :/

beside the worst anniversary reward, actually this is the only game i play in my phone not because i don't have any storage again. But i just being real this is my most comfort game all the time, thanks mihoyo. But i remind again that the most player likes any reward so mihoyo can give us more ehe :D

The opacity change on Raiden's ring is kind of annoying. I preferred the older brighter one. Would be good if this ring gets brighter when the stacks reach maximum. Now it just looks like there's an eternal fog on my screen.

No more money spent on this game, dont give this game your money, spend wisely it's not worth it. I've been playing this game for a year you can still pull the characters you want just by saving primogems no need to spend so much money to just c6 a character with bug and misleading description on constellation, unless you're rich and have nothing to spend your money on, but that is still ill advice to spend money on digital currency to get a 2d/3d characters,When you can just buy a triple A game

I like the game at first due to good plot and rewards... But as the game goes the story becomes less interesting and right now on inazuma I experienced less events. Also reruns on the banner aren't fair. Hope the devs will look at the suggestions of players and listen to them. Aside from that it's a good game. An open world where you can play with friends even as free to play players.

I love a lot about this game, but the gacha system is so trash. Especially the weapon banner pity and the epitomized fate points. The fate points were put there to help but they're basically useless for any non whale players. You need to get not one but two five star weapons, nevermind if you're trying to get the character as well, and if you lose the pity on the epitomized path, that fate point doesn't even count on the next weapon banner. So in total, for a WEAPON ONLY, you'd need 270 wishes.

The game is great and enjoyable,the stories are good too. But, there is something that bother me, the archon quest seems going too fast, you can save another archon quest story for the next update or develop it more so there will be more story for every updates.

One of the best Open world games I have ever played. The storyline is amazing and the music is just top notch. I cannot ask for more then this for a free game. The characters are really fun and interesting however some downsights would be there are no balance patches and the game has no end game content so if you're a new player the game will be really fun but later it gets a little boring

Greatest mobile game so far. Just some problems. The Resin limit is getting stupid after a while. It's making the world level is becoming annoying. You cannot exactly choose your world level limit, so to deal with new area you have to grind your characters, but again limited by the resin system that really i don't see why it is necessary. Also is the developer really ignored all the players comments and suggestions? Please let the character to be able to interact with all the cats and dogs.

This game is rly beautiful and fun to play. It's one of the game that blow people's mind. But I'll state this one common issue : we need a mid-high spec devices to play this game. I tried to play on mobile but I can't even go into the game, I keep going back and forth on the loading screen. And it needs so much storage that I need to clear up my entire phone so there's literally just this game in my phone. And now at 2.2 update my phone cannot handle this game's storage requirement anymore.

Honestly, I don't even know why people are complaining on the anniversary rewards. They still have to make money, so I get it. If you're short on primogems, you could just do the spiral abyss. Get to level 9, do every available floor, and then you're set. You literally get 1200 gems per week if you can get to floor 12. It's that easy.

Genshin impact is a pretty fun game, the anniversary rewards may be not that good but it's fine to me cuz i only want to enjoy the game and the reason that i give only 4 stars bc of the bugs and some giltch it always happen to me like sometimes it automatically leave the game while i literally did nothing to it but after all it was a pretty fun game, the story are very interesting, please keep going! (i may come back and give 5 stars if the bugs and giltch fixed)

well, i have to say that the stories, the way how Mihoyo created to play is extremely incredible. But i think it won't last long, cause the weapon banner drove me crazy and furious. I can't even roll for me a favorite weapon as other players do. It keeps deviating, not just the first time, but 3 times already! Each time is 80 rolls :) **** you

Ever since the new update, it keeps crashing and crashing and won't even let me play the game and if it let me play the game, it is really really slow and becomes quite frustrating. The older versions are a lot better than this.

They focus on quick buck instead of player retention. Worst anniversary. Manipulative marketing, limited deals they promote are worth nothing. Progression system is aweful, it's gated as hell and give very little possibly for upgrading your stuff each day. End game is non existing basically. No matter how much you spend you have no guarantee on getting everything or even the stuff you want. Too many items are behind a pay gatcha wall so there's little to no things you can get through gameplay.
replyContent: We'd like to thank all Travelers for your continued support and love of Genshin Impact! We will continue to provide you with more high-quality game content. If Travelers encounter problems during their adventures, please don't hesitate to contact us via the in-game feedback channel. Your gaming experience and suggestions are always important to us.

content: Notwithstanding the issue with the anniversary event, the game is enjoyable, especially to those who like good stories, characters, and exploring. Combat mechanics are easy to grasp although certain reactions are more favoured than others.
It was a fun game. am stuck on progress about a month new content is unavailable to me until I complete an extremely difficult mission. My past review vanished.

My friend been losing 50/50 straight for a year. Which is not fair for him. While other get a chance to win 50/50. Losing 50/50 after spend some money on this game felt so unrewarding. Not to mention both 5 star get on hard pity (70+ pulls). Unless Mihoyo remove this scam move which is 50/50 chances, i will rate this game low. Also after 1 year playing this game, im started losing my excitement because of lack end game content. Not to mention artifact drops is punishing enough to suffer.

I'am F2P, this game is 100% not pay to win. This MMORPG is very capable for solo player. Even if you don't get a *5 hero or *5 weap, you can still survive. Free game with beautiful graphic when you can adventure. I think, low ratings only come from players don't want to play little hard and compare their accounts with other players. I've been playing for a year. The first half year I don't have a *5 hero or weap, because I don't understand the gacha mechanism yet. But I still can clear all quest

Absolutely amazing game! Fell in love with it almost instantly. The graphics are amazing the detail is amazing and the characters and heroes are just absolutely wonderful. Really well designed game and looking forward to future updates

It's a great game. The graphics are beautiful, the character designs are great and the different play styles of each character, too. The mechanic of the combination of the elements allows you to play it in your own way. The story is great and very interesting and the events are fun to play.
The game is really good! I love the story line, the va, the graphic, the bosses, and the 1st anniversary gifts, I don't know why people hate the 1st anniversary gifts smh
Game was initially fun but eventually became a grind with no end game content (except for spiral abyss). I miss enjoying the game, and hope for more end game content.
replyContent: We sincerely apologize for your unsatisfactory experience, Traveler. If you have any feedback or suggestions, please send us an email or contact Customer Service via in-game feedback to help us improve the game.

content: Genshin is a fun game if you're willing to grind to upgrade weapons and artifacts. I like the storyline as well as the music and visuals. its entirely possible to play this f2p as long as you're willing to put in time. The primogems and stuff are very expensive but hey thats life. The content comes out at a good rate and there are a lot of events and things between updates. The people who tanked their ratings are just throwing tantrums.

Superb soundtrack and a Great game. But most of the time bug fix being rolled out are not the requested items to be fixed. There is an in-game survey but it seems that the rosponse from the survey are not being taken into considerarion at all.

The game itself is very entertaining. The art is really good and so is the soundtrack. One complaint is that there's too many bugs (thus the 4 star) but other than that I'm really enjoying the game even though I've been playing for a year.

This game is really good at the beginning but the late game rewards just keep getting worse , even the anniversary rewards were disappointing . The devs are not paying attention even after so many complains from the community , and this isn't even the first time they have often ignored the community and never fixed their game properly hopefully after they realize their mistake we can atleast the game alive again

This game was really fun and the charecter animations were really cool and detailed! The bosses were also very detailed! I would recommend this game if you like adventure games! But I lost my account today and I don't know why! I think my account reset

I absolutely adore this game, its amazing to play, the graphics are exceptional and love the freedom of exploration given. However the one problem I do experience that the resin system is terrible and farming artifacts often relies on luck which I do not have. I do not think it should be this luck based for good artifacts because it makes it very difficult for both F2P and casual players to do enough damage to have fun playing the game...

content: After playing for 1 year, Genshin Impact is an amazing game at the surface level. Great world-building, character designs, combat system, story, and graphics. However, going deeper into the game, it has many glaring issues that haven't been addressed. Lack of endgame content, high effort for low rewards, QoL changes, resin system, artifact RNG, overpriced gacha, and the recent downgrading of story and characters. The game becomes increasingly disappointing and a daily chore in the end.

But when I saw how underwhelming the new 5* characters were, especially Yoimiya and Kokomi, and the lack of any response from miHoYo despite the community having made in-depth analyses and being pretty vocal about their flaws, the rushed storyline, and now the anniversary rewards, I feel like they don't care about us the players at all. content: I've been playing for about a year now and it gets less and less enjoyable, ESPECIALLY because of the new puzzles in the new areas. There are too many and they're too difficult to understand sometimes, especially since you don't encounter anything that explains the (new) mechanisms. Some of the newly added features feel like a useless burden that only take up storage and make the game feel less like itself and the gacha system is designed to only appeal to the company itself and "whales".

The game is still great for me, new events, new characters and reruns, great lore, and interesting game mechanics. I just can't give a 5 star yet because Mihoyo still doesn't know how to respond to its player base. I just hope this improves in the future.

content: The open-world experience is notable for a mobile game. Exploration can be fun, and small rewards are often given for careful searching. This is Genshin at its best, in the early/mid game. Though the developers have said that they will listen to feedback in the future, it remains to be seen whether or not they will keep their word. Large parts of the community have been complaining about certain issues for months or even since launch. Some of these issues are simple quality of life changes, some are skills that don't work as described, such as Xinyan's skill not always counting the number of targets hit properly, which has been bugged since December 2020. New characters' kits have felt like a mishmash of concepts that don't work together as a complete kit, such as Yoimiya's burst and level 2 charge attack for her skill and normal-attack-based playstyle, not to mention the minimal AOE for a character based around fireworks. Others are borderline unplayable without constellations, such as Kujou Sara without C2. I love the exploring world, the music and the lore, but the gameplay of some of these new characters just don't have the polish that many of the other characters have had in the past, and some clearly are designed in ways to milk as much money as they can out of the playerbase with the strength of early constellations. Until I see action based on community feedback or a change in design philosophy, I will maintain this 1-star review.

Been with this game for nearly a year now and really have enjoyed it. Many are complaining about the anniversary rewards that was merely the final straw. As a low spender, the game is just a grind. I've finished all the main quests in about a week and In the lame game I have nothing to do except farm. The farming is limited by resin (which is the equivalent of energy) so I'm at a point where I can only farm a certain amount per day unless I pay. There are many ways to incentivize paying but when it costs around 15$ to fill up energy that you can blow through in an hour or so trying to farm, I can't justify continuing to play. It's too limiting.

content: Could've been a great game, BUT hampered by trash artifact and resin systems. Crit substats, the most important substats, have the 2nd lowest chance to roll. And Resin will limit you to 20mins of play time daily. I'm still playing as a welkin only player cause of sunk cost bias and genuine curiosity for the story, but I don't recommend it for those who have not started. Try playing when all nations have been released.

I play the game for it's beautiful story, open world and fun events, and moonchase have been a total blast so no complains about the story and event aspect. But I have some issues with puzzle mechanics character AIs and kits. 1. Some of the open world puzzles are hard as heck and I get headache solving them, I wanna have fun in exploration but this sometimes spoils the fun for me. 2. I don't have many character but I always use venti and the AI of his Q sucks, god knows how many ults I have wasted just because it wouldn't focus towards the enemies or where the larger group of enemies are and I believe it needs serious fixing. Also bow characters or characters in general when fighting enemies like cicin mages, they always attack the cicins when I want then to attack the mage and it's annoying and sometimes when there are enemies on either side of the character it attacks the other enemy rather that the one I'm facing. 3. Character kits- As I said I don't use many characters so I'll only talk about few characters. Yoimiya- She's one of my favorite characters and the thing I don't like about her gameplay is her E. In combat, during her E when she needs healing or the shield expires, you swap out and her E goes to waste. I'd be really happy if the pyro infusion of her E doesn't expire when you swap out like Diluc's so that I can use her E freely. Kokomi- Kokomi's kit is really unique but the problem is that we exchange 100% crit rate which is really valuable for only 25% healing bonus? At least make it 50 or 75% if not 100. And since she can't crit, hydro dmg bonus is not a very good ascension stat, she can have healing bonus like Qiqi or Jean or even can be the first character have HP% as ascension stat since her kit is so unique. I wanna give it a 5* because I absolutely love this game but the above issues bother me so much. I'll be glad if they get fixed.

Game is good at the start however as the version number increases, bugs start to pile up and get ignored by the developers. One more thing is TO BRING BACK WINDTRACE EVENT or make something similar, I am antisocial even online but windtrace made me wanna join the fun.

content: Low spender day 1 player. Genshin starts out beautifully with a gorgeous open world and the initial storyline are great. Once you hit the endgame tgh, the experience takes a nosedive. The endgame = spending a few minutes farming artifacts (99% [not an exaggeration] of which are unusable) in a world with nothing to do. At that point the game becomes an exercise in frustration that leaves you feeling empty which encourages folks to spend to fill the void and get a sense of progress. Buyer beware!

content: Amazing game! The open-world, exploration, gameplay, music, and characters are all top-notch. The story and lore are also really building up in the latest updates. It's hard to believe that this game is free to play. True, this is a gacha game, but this aspect is far from necessary to enjoy everything Genshin Impact has to offer. There have been some growing pains with launch players catching up with content too quickly, but there are consistent events to keep things interesting.

Gacha rates are horrible as well as RNG for farming artifacts and ascension mats. As for the story, I found the main story quests quite poor especially in the Inazuma update. Some side quests even surpass the main scenario in terms of quality. Also, this game suffers a lot from unnecessarily long dialogues be it main, side, or daily quests. MHY needs to fix these.

"Honestly one of the best games that I've played in a while." This was my original review almost a year ago, however, I have to change it. The game's content is still great, however it is optimized poorly. It is extremely heavy; I have to uninstall a bunch of my apps just to make space for it. Even then it still lags and loads very slowly. I would like for the game to get back to its original glory.

The gameplay leveling system? Iffy. They need to redo the abysmal resin system and (statistically PROVEN) rigged artifact rates. Alotof your character leveling is locked behind rng. The game demands more material from you than the amount it gives. The resin cost needs to be either reduced for each domain/boss, drastically increased recharge rate of resin, or add more sources for fragile resin. Update:With the new banner system, there NEEDS to be more sources for primos. Horribly unbalanced!

Honest and true comments from a person who starting playing games since mid-80's. All-in-all, in fairness, Genshin Impact is a mediocre game in the modern era. This is because modern meta gaming (ie. which is basically going full speed and see who finishes the game first to get into end game content, then start complaining why there is not enough content) requires a game to really have an in-depth end-game content and also satisfy both softcore and hardcore players. However, Mihoyo was not able to deliver that hardcore aspect, leading to this game being really just a waifu owning game at the end. Pros: - contains a simplistic battling system with low learning curve that ensures a diversity of audiences can get engaged into investing in the game - Non-linear, explorative as a play-at-your-own-pace style - Mercy system is clearly stated in place as a Gacha game Cons: - Chore feeling. Like everyone says. You log in and spend stamina, do your dailies, and events if any (see below) - Events are limited to the same "mechanics" - its either you repeat, time-gated, or fulfill requirements. - Character modelling is heavily reused. 90% of the characters that holds the same weapon uses the same animation model. - Character development is mediocre. - NO end game raid (Abyss isn't really considered one) - Not invested in in-depth multiplayer system. No scaling if different world travels over in a lower level, makes multiplayer boring.
